Jotty is a self-hosted, privacy-focused productivity platform combining
notes, checklists and a knowledge base in a single web application.

Key features:
- Rich-text editor (TipTap) with Markdown, tables, tasks and code blocks
- Excalidraw whiteboard and Drawio diagram embedding
- Encrypted notes (OpenPGP / libsodium)
- OIDC / SSO authentication with optional local-account fallback
- TOTP two-factor authentication
- Git-tracked note history
- WebSocket-based real-time collaboration
- PWA support for offline use
- LDAP / Active Directory integration
- Theming and i18n (multiple locales)

The application is a Next.js 16 app using the standalone output mode.  On
FreeBSD, SWC native binaries are unavailable; the port patches node_modules
at build time to substitute a WASM fallback and force the webpack bundler.

WWW: https://github.com/fccview/jotty
